com.vector.cfg.util.activity.execresult

Interface IExecutionResult

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDebugable, IUserMessage

    @ThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IExecutionResult
extends IUserMessage, IDebugable
    The class IExecutionResult represents the outcome of an operation.

    Please use the class ExecutionResultBuilder to construct object which implements the IExecutionResult interface.

    (c) Copyright Vctr Informatik GmbH. All Rights Reserved.

    See Also:
    IActivity, IActivityResult, IActivityState

      • isOk

        @PublishedMethod
boolean isOk()
        Returns true, if the getEffectiveExecutionResult() is either EExecutionResult.SUCCESSFUL or EExecutionResult.WARNING.

        Returns false, if any error has occurred.

        Returns:
        true, if the execution was successful.

        java.lang.String toDebugString()
